The paper discusses the use of rational kernels in statistical learning techniques for sequence data, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on kernel-based learning techniques. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of rational kernels in text data. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the representation of sequences. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of rational kernels in image data. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of rational kernels in various domains of AI.
